HEADWORD: Biauriculate
<hw>Bi`au*ric"u*late</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>auriculate</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having two auricles, as the heart of mammals,
birds, and reptiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Having two earlike
projections at its base, as a leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Biaxial</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Biaxal</ent>⟦br⟧
